			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><b><a href="http://www.sff.net/people/nankress/">By Nancy Kress.</a></b><br />
Read by Sheri Mann Stewart.<br />
First appeared in <a href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0756402441/escapepod-20">Stars: Stories Based On Janis Ian Songs</a>, ed. Janis Ian &amp; Mike Resnick.</p>

<p><i>Mia didn&#8217;t reply.  Her attention was riveted to Esefeb.  The girl flung herself up the stairs and sat up in bed, facing the wall.  What Mia had see before could hardly be called a smile compared to the light, the sheer joy, that illuminated Esefeb&#8217;s face now.  Esefeb shuddered in ecstasy, crooning to the empty wall.</i></p>

<p><i>&#8220;Ej-es.  Ej-es.  Aaahhhh, Ej-es!&#8221;</i></p>

<p><i>Mia turned away.  She was a medician, but Esefeb&#8217;s emotion seemed too private to witness.  It was the ecstasy of orgasm, or religious transfiguration, or madness.</i></p>

<p><i>&#8220;Mia,&#8221; her wrister said, &#8220;I need an image of that girl&#8217;s brain.&#8221;</i></p>

<p><b>Rated PG</b>.  Contains passing sexual references and graphic medical description.</p>

