			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><b><a href="http://www.jlake.com">By Jay Lake.</a></b><br />
Read by Stephen Eley.<br />
First appeared in <b>3SF Magazine</b>, October 2002.</p>

<p><i>That spring in math class, after we&#8217;d all kind of got back to normal about the </i>Challenger<i> blowing up, we were studying angles.  Because I do good in class, Mrs. Doornie gave me a protractor to work with, and I used it to measure the angle of my dreams.  That&#8217;s when I figured exactly how steep a hill needed to be for me to fly in real life.</i></p>

